fr.inria.atlanmod.mogwai.datastore.pipes

Interface PipesDatastore<D,E,R,A>

  • Type Parameters:
    D - the type of the data source to use
    T - the type representing model elements
    L - the type representing references
    P - the type representing attributes' value
    All Superinterfaces:
    ModelDatastore<D,E,R,A>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AutocommitNeoEMFGraphDatastore, NeoEMFGraphDatastore

    public interface PipesDatastore<D,E,R,A>
extends ModelDatastore<D,E,R,A>
    Refines ModelDatastore by providing methods that should be implemented to manipulate a data source as a model streamed in the Pipes framework.

    This mapping is used by the Mogwa√Ø-ATL engine to navigate a model and compute ATL transformations based on the Gremlin traversal query language

    Methods of this mapping are Pipes' wrappers around the low-level API defined in ModelDatastore. This API does not define the current element (labeled from in ModelDatastore) as a method parameter, and compute the associated operation on all the element in the current GremlinPipeline, returning a Pipe or a Pipeline (see Pipe website for further information).

    Author:
    Gwendal DANIEL
    See Also:
    ModelDatastore
